# Issues — core rules

Follow [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) and existing code in the same package.

## Stack

- Quarkus REST + Hibernate ORM + PostgreSQL + Flyway.
- Angular SPA via Quinoa (`src/main/webui/`).
- JWT auth (SmallRye JWT); API base path `/api`.

## Endpoints

- `@ApplicationScoped` + `@Path`; suffix `*Endpoint`.
- Constructor injection for repositories and services.
- HTTP body types: Java `record`, suffix `Request` / `Response` — [issues-http-contract.mdc](issues-http-contract.mdc).
- Response mapping: static `load()` factory on `*Response` records.
- Security: `@DenyAll` on class + `@RolesAllowed` on methods for protected resources.

## Data access

- Repositories: `EntityManager` directly; `Optional` for single results; `@Transactional` on mutating methods — [issues-jpa.mdc](issues-jpa.mdc).
- Non-trivial domain logic: `@ApplicationScoped` `*Service` (e.g. `TicketHistoryService`, `MailerService`).
- Cross-cutting notifications: CDI events + SSE in `notifications`.

## Frontend

- Services in `src/main/webui/src/app/services/` — HTTP calls to `/api`.
- Components by feature folder under `components/`.
- Auth: `auth.guard.ts`, `auth.interceptor.ts` for Bearer token.

## Never

- `System.out.println` — use SLF4J.
- Raw `VO`/`DTO` suffix on HTTP types.
- Hardcode new API paths in multiple Angular files — centralize in services.

## When adding a feature

ARCHITECTURE.md §12 — domain spec → package → tests → endpoint → Angular service/component → feature catalog.

## When fixing a test

Understand failure first; fix production code or test data via `Given`. Do not weaken assertions.
